1
00:00:00,720 --> 00:00:01,820
Wataru.

2
00:00:04,330 --> 00:00:05,480
What's wrong?

3
00:00:06,460 --> 00:00:07,560
I'm sorry.

4
00:00:08,710 --> 00:00:10,670
If you don't want this,
you can push me away.

5
00:00:19,060 --> 00:00:19,640
Wait...

6
00:00:19,641 --> 00:00:21,060
What are you doing?

7
00:00:21,980 --> 00:00:22,890
What if someone comes?

8
00:00:22,940 --> 00:00:24,520
Yeah... I know.

9
00:01:00,360 --> 00:01:01,360
I'm sorry.

10
00:01:08,940 --> 00:01:11,480
His feelings and sincerity...

11
00:01:14,260 --> 00:01:16,320
I can feel them so deeply, and yet...

12
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:23,450
I guess I still can't do this.

13
00:01:25,180 --> 00:01:27,880
That lonely look he gets sometimes...

14
00:01:30,250 --> 00:01:31,460
Why is that?

15
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:44,840
Here.

16
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:47,280
Wait a minute.
Where did that voice come from?

17
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:49,139
You startled me.

18
00:01:49,140 --> 00:01:52,080
You looked lost in thought.
Is something on your mind?

19
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:53,650
It's nothing.

20
00:01:54,650 --> 00:01:55,650
Thanks.

21
00:01:58,120 --> 00:02:01,840
How can Saeki act so normal
after making a request like that?

22
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:10,060
So, when can we go to the beach
from the final scene?

23
00:02:10,196 --> 00:02:11,776
Oh... the pilgrimage?

24
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:12,630
Yeah.

25
00:02:12,631 --> 00:02:14,590
That's the last spot, right?

26
00:02:16,900 --> 00:02:19,230
With part-time work and homework...

27
00:02:20,640 --> 00:02:24,500
The only day I can clear my schedule
is the twenty-eighth.

28
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:25,819
The twenty-eighth?

29
00:02:25,820 --> 00:02:26,820
Yeah.

30
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:30,239
Does that work for you?

31
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:32,790
- Let's make it the twenty-eighth then.
- Sounds good.

32
00:02:33,480 --> 00:02:35,720
That cave is really amazing.

33
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:37,080
It left a huge impression on me.

34
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:40,880
That's the place I want to visit most.

35
00:02:42,910 --> 00:02:44,540
I can't wait.

36
00:02:45,673 --> 00:02:48,903
By the way,
once this deal is over...

37
00:02:49,210 --> 00:02:51,000
what will happen to us?

38
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:52,600
(Take care.)

39
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:57,600
(No...!)

40
00:03:02,099 --> 00:03:03,099
(Let go of me.)

41
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:06,900
(I don't want to... pleaes don't go)

42
00:03:08,100 --> 00:03:09,200
(I'm sorry...)

43
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:13,800
(You're not in my heart anymore.)

44
00:03:26,760 --> 00:03:30,990
To Saeki, this is probably
just a way to get closure.

45
00:03:32,760 --> 00:03:37,020
Once this is all over,
we'll just go back to how we were...

46
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,200
(Goodbye.)

47
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:49,500
One day, he'll stop liking me.

48
00:03:51,880 --> 00:03:53,420
If that happens...

49
00:03:55,580 --> 00:03:56,940
If that happens...

50
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:10,500
If that happens...

51
00:04:13,880 --> 00:04:15,040
I'll be so lonely.

52
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:50,800
"My Summer Of You"
(Episode 4)

53
00:05:51,840 --> 00:05:56,290
Typhoon No. 4 is expected
to bring strong winds...

54
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:59,140
- with potential warning-level heavy rain.
- Saeki?

55
00:05:59,860 --> 00:06:01,320
It's no use.

56
00:06:02,520 --> 00:06:04,990
The trains to Moriya Beach are suspended.

57
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:09,530
Even though it's barely
windy or rainy here.

58
00:06:10,980 --> 00:06:11,980
Yeah.

59
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:14,400
There's nothing we can do about a typhoon.

60
00:06:15,330 --> 00:06:18,080
It suddenly changed course.

61
00:06:18,100 --> 00:06:19,200
Damn it.

62
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:21,900
I wanted to go even if it rained,

63
00:06:22,620 --> 00:06:24,480
but it really is too dangerous.

64
00:06:24,520 --> 00:06:25,670
What a shame.

65
00:06:30,090 --> 00:06:34,110
Then do you want to come
over and watch "Sea of Light"?

66
00:06:35,280 --> 00:06:36,299
Huh?

67
00:06:36,300 --> 00:06:41,300
Well, since we have the day off,
I thought you could come over.

68
00:06:41,540 --> 00:06:44,100
Oh, or I could go to your place instead.

69
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:46,660
No, I'll go to yours.

70
00:06:47,190 --> 00:06:49,250
My place is a bit of a mess right now.

71
00:06:49,880 --> 00:06:50,660
Is it?

72
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:51,660
Yeah.

73
00:06:52,660 --> 00:06:56,850
Though my room is pretty messy too.

74
00:06:57,370 --> 00:06:58,580
Whatever, it's fine.

75
00:06:58,620 --> 00:07:00,520
I'll text you my address.

76
00:07:01,260 --> 00:07:03,000
Okay, I'll head over now.

77
00:07:09,100 --> 00:07:12,140
Alright, time to clean up.

78
00:07:13,260 --> 00:07:14,300
Okay...

79
00:07:14,840 --> 00:07:15,840
Oh my god.

80
00:07:16,760 --> 00:07:19,200
Underwear... Why is there
underwear all over the floor?

81
00:07:23,680 --> 00:07:26,680
- Come on in.
- Thanks for having me.

82
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:30,560
This room is so you, Wataru.

83
00:07:34,880 --> 00:07:36,430
Stop staring.

84
00:07:41,060 --> 00:07:45,339
Showing someone your room feels as
embarrassing as letting them see you naked.

85
00:07:45,340 --> 00:07:46,359
Naked?

86
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:48,629
No, I mean my interests and tastes.

87
00:07:48,630 --> 00:07:51,560
It feels like my mind
is completely exposed.

88
00:07:52,220 --> 00:07:53,640
I know.

89
00:07:56,460 --> 00:07:57,840
Oh, sorry.

90
00:07:58,500 --> 00:07:59,500
This...

91
00:08:00,640 --> 00:08:01,720
Huh...?

92
00:08:03,150 --> 00:08:04,450
Ah! I'm sorry!

93
00:08:15,740 --> 00:08:16,940
I'm sorry.

94
00:08:37,930 --> 00:08:39,850
Excuse me.

95
00:08:43,260 --> 00:08:45,190
- Excuse me.
- Wait, wait!

96
00:08:45,230 --> 00:08:46,519
It's not what it looks like!
It's a total misunderstanding!

97
00:08:46,520 --> 00:08:48,600
Look, this was on the floor...

98
00:08:48,690 --> 00:08:49,730
Underwear?

99
00:08:50,100 --> 00:08:53,120
He tried to grab the underwear I picked up,
and we both tripped and fell.

100
00:08:54,660 --> 00:08:56,920
Oh, I see.

101
00:08:56,980 --> 00:08:59,180
Sorry about that.
My brother is such a slob.

102
00:08:59,990 --> 00:09:01,890
Oh, I'm Wataru's older sister.

103
00:09:02,040 --> 00:09:02,980
I'm Saeki.

104
00:09:03,060 --> 00:09:04,619
Sorry for dropping by so suddenly.

105
00:09:04,620 --> 00:09:05,820
Don't worry about it.

106
00:09:06,440 --> 00:09:08,749
Mom said to give you guys this.

107
00:09:08,750 --> 00:09:11,000
Oh, thank you.

108
00:09:16,900 --> 00:09:19,400
Sis, we're going to watch a movie.
Get out already.

109
00:09:20,280 --> 00:09:21,679
Have fun, Saeki.

110
00:09:21,680 --> 00:09:23,390
Get out, hurry up.

111
00:09:30,480 --> 00:09:33,490
- Let's start watching.
- Yeah.

112
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:35,567
"Sea of Light"

113
00:09:43,520 --> 00:09:45,339
It really is the best.

114
00:09:45,340 --> 00:09:47,460
Yeah, it's great no matter
how many times I watch it.

115
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:49,619
But watching it makes
me want to go even more.

116
00:09:49,620 --> 00:09:50,699
To the beach from the final scene.

117
00:09:50,700 --> 00:09:51,700
Yeah.

118
00:09:52,130 --> 00:09:54,200
By the way, I missed
the Tonkatsu Pavilion guy.

119
00:09:54,230 --> 00:09:55,360
Oh, I forgot about that.

120
00:09:57,360 --> 00:09:59,340
Let's look for him next time.

121
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:02,020
Yeah...

122
00:10:09,190 --> 00:10:11,220
The typhoon seems weaker than I expected.

123
00:10:12,020 --> 00:10:13,020
Yeah.

124
00:10:14,300 --> 00:10:17,700
Hey, let's reschedule
once school starts.

125
00:10:18,060 --> 00:10:20,140
We really have to go there
for this to feel complete.

126
00:10:21,620 --> 00:10:23,680
Wataru, you can stop here.

127
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:25,450
I can walk the rest of the way.

128
00:10:26,040 --> 00:10:27,040
Okay.

129
00:10:27,290 --> 00:10:30,120
Well... see you next semester.

130
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,600
Get home safe.

131
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:37,210
Saeki?

132
00:10:39,180 --> 00:10:42,000
Wataru, thank you.

133
00:10:45,700 --> 00:10:46,800
For what?

134
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:48,620
I didn't do anything.

135
00:10:50,260 --> 00:10:51,360
See ya.

136
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:07,870
Even so, thank you.

137
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:32,790
Morning, Wataru.

138
00:11:33,880 --> 00:11:35,079
Did you enjoy your summer?

139
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:37,400
Of course I did.
It was summer, after all.

140
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:39,560
You idiot.

141
00:11:39,940 --> 00:11:41,200
By "enjoying summer,".

142
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:43,880
I mean "falling in love."

143
00:11:43,950 --> 00:11:44,700
Get it?

144
00:11:44,701 --> 00:11:47,090
No way. Enjoying summer
means working up a sweat in youth.

145
00:11:48,760 --> 00:11:50,000
That makes absolutely no sense.

146
00:11:50,210 --> 00:11:51,000
None at all.

147
00:11:51,040 --> 00:11:52,040
Hey.

148
00:12:17,290 --> 00:12:18,360
Are you looking for Saeki?

149
00:12:18,730 --> 00:12:19,730
Huh?

150
00:12:20,440 --> 00:12:22,600
You've been staring at the
hallway since this morning.

151
00:12:26,190 --> 00:12:29,660
I just heard from a
friend in the other class...

152
00:12:29,750 --> 00:12:31,830
that Saeki is absent today.

153
00:12:32,450 --> 00:12:34,040
Apparently, it's due to family matters.

154
00:12:34,960 --> 00:12:36,189
Family matters?

155
00:12:36,190 --> 00:12:37,850
That's what the homeroom teacher said.

156
00:12:39,230 --> 00:12:40,770
Did Saeki mention anything to you?

157
00:12:44,260 --> 00:12:45,340
No.

158
00:12:51,980 --> 00:12:53,660
Sorry for texting when I know you're busy.

159
00:12:53,730 --> 00:12:55,790
I heard you were absent today too.
I'm worried.

160
00:12:56,610 --> 00:12:59,170
If there's anything I can do,
please let me know.

161
00:13:01,490 --> 00:13:03,200
It's already been three days.

162
00:13:07,370 --> 00:13:08,700
Alright.

163
00:13:36,190 --> 00:13:37,249
I'm so sleepy...

164
00:13:37,250 --> 00:13:39,829
I can't survive two more periods.

165
00:13:39,830 --> 00:13:43,330
What are you guys talking about?

166
00:13:43,970 --> 00:13:45,510
Summer is over.

167
00:13:45,550 --> 00:13:47,610
Now is the season for studying.

168
00:13:49,470 --> 00:13:50,700
- Goodnight.
- Hey.

169
00:13:54,950 --> 00:13:56,230
Excuse me, do you have a second?

170
00:13:58,610 --> 00:14:00,230
You're Toda, right?

171
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:04,050
- Yeah.
- I'm Kawaguchi from Class A.

172
00:14:04,750 --> 00:14:07,780
Toda, you're always with Saeki, right?

173
00:14:08,680 --> 00:14:10,550
I guess so.

174
00:14:11,050 --> 00:14:12,760
Did you hear about that?

175
00:14:13,590 --> 00:14:14,590
About what?

176
00:14:14,870 --> 00:14:16,580
Wait, seriously?

177
00:14:16,970 --> 00:14:18,130
Even you don't know, Toda?

178
00:14:18,710 --> 00:14:22,210
He's been absent since
the semester started, right?

179
00:14:24,030 --> 00:14:25,170
Yeah, I think so.

180
00:14:25,730 --> 00:14:28,450
Well, the homeroom
teacher announced it today.

181
00:14:31,250 --> 00:14:34,260
He transferred schools.

182
00:14:37,330 --> 00:14:40,310
Apparently, it was decided
suddenly over summer break.

183
00:14:40,350 --> 00:14:42,070
I tried calling him, but he didn't pick up.

184
00:14:42,230 --> 00:14:45,020
I thought you might know something,
so I came to ask.

185
00:14:46,330 --> 00:14:47,650
Do you know anything?

186
00:14:49,930 --> 00:14:51,070
Toda?

187
00:14:52,430 --> 00:14:53,430
Hey.

188
00:14:56,590 --> 00:14:57,590
Toda?

189
00:15:15,210 --> 00:15:21,540
The phone you are calling may be turned off
or out of the coverage area.

190
00:15:39,070 --> 00:15:41,229
Please tell me where he moved.

191
00:15:41,230 --> 00:15:42,940
You really don't give up, do you?

192
00:15:42,980 --> 00:15:44,289
Can you really not tell me?

193
00:15:44,290 --> 00:15:47,030
Like I said,
I can't give you that information.

194
00:15:47,130 --> 00:15:48,640
It's a matter of personal privacy.

195
00:15:48,780 --> 00:15:50,359
Just ask him yourself.

196
00:15:50,360 --> 00:15:52,570
But I can't get in touch with him.

197
00:15:54,450 --> 00:15:55,590
Please.

198
00:15:58,120 --> 00:16:01,310
You two are as stubborn as they come.

199
00:16:04,250 --> 00:16:06,400
I'll only tell you what I'm allowed to.
Is that okay?

200
00:16:07,690 --> 00:16:08,690
Yes.

201
00:16:09,510 --> 00:16:10,910
Well, how should I put this...

202
00:16:13,220 --> 00:16:15,150
It's true that he's transferring.

203
00:16:15,750 --> 00:16:18,220
But he's actually moving to Canada.

204
00:16:19,850 --> 00:16:20,950
Canada?

205
00:16:21,610 --> 00:16:22,610
Yes.

206
00:16:22,730 --> 00:16:26,160
I heard his father is being stationed
there, so he has to go with him.

207
00:16:26,990 --> 00:16:30,560
But this wasn't decided over summer break.
It was already set during the first semester.

208
00:16:31,490 --> 00:16:32,490
What?

209
00:16:33,050 --> 00:16:35,846
He asked me to keep it a secret
until the start of the second semester.

210
00:16:35,870 --> 00:16:39,490
I tried to talk him out of it,
asking if he was really okay with this.

211
00:16:39,890 --> 00:16:42,560
But he was extremely
firm and wouldn't budge.

212
00:16:44,050 --> 00:16:47,730
Since he was so determined,
I couldn't force him.

213
00:16:48,110 --> 00:16:50,690
He must have had his reasons.

214
00:16:52,930 --> 00:16:54,990
I'm sorry, but I can't
tell you where he moved.

215
00:16:56,090 --> 00:16:58,160
Because I made a promise to him.

216
00:16:58,850 --> 00:17:00,600
That's all I can say.

217
00:17:21,050 --> 00:17:22,250
So that's how it was.

218
00:17:23,120 --> 00:17:27,680
The person I like
is the Wataru right in front of me.

219
00:17:28,790 --> 00:17:30,290
Even his confession to me...

220
00:17:32,350 --> 00:17:36,510
But in return, I have a favor to ask.
Would that be okay?

221
00:17:36,810 --> 00:17:38,820
Even proposing that trade-off...

222
00:17:40,430 --> 00:17:42,030
Everything up until now...

223
00:17:44,490 --> 00:17:45,490
All of it...

224
00:17:49,210 --> 00:17:50,750
So that's what it was all about.

225
00:17:52,590 --> 00:17:55,420
Is Wataru going to be okay?

226
00:17:55,490 --> 00:17:56,920
Who knows?

227
00:17:58,410 --> 00:18:00,910
I don't know what Saeki's situation is,

228
00:18:02,490 --> 00:18:04,500
but those two were really close.

229
00:18:05,450 --> 00:18:08,140
Leaving without saying a word...
It must be really hard on him.

230
00:18:10,270 --> 00:18:11,810
Oh, Wataru is back.

231
00:18:26,980 --> 00:18:28,760
Want to go to the batting cages?

232
00:18:29,220 --> 00:18:30,220
Huh?

233
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:33,730
I feel like I haven't gotten
any exercise in ages.

234
00:18:35,380 --> 00:18:37,110
- Oh.
- Sure.

235
00:18:37,140 --> 00:18:38,169
- Let's go then.
- Let's do it!

236
00:18:38,170 --> 00:18:39,530
I want to hit too.

237
00:18:41,060 --> 00:18:42,950
- Awesome!
- What speed are you going for?

238
00:18:42,990 --> 00:18:45,640
150 km/h, of course!

239
00:18:58,800 --> 00:19:00,180
Damn it!

240
00:19:10,620 --> 00:19:13,270
Wataru, turn down the speed!

241
00:19:13,660 --> 00:19:15,070
No, this is fine.

242
00:20:04,900 --> 00:20:05,900
I like you.

243
00:20:26,640 --> 00:20:27,839
He hit it! He hit it!

244
00:20:27,840 --> 00:20:29,180
A grand slam!

245
00:20:29,860 --> 00:20:31,100
That's amazing!

246
00:20:32,960 --> 00:20:34,160
Wataru?

247
00:20:36,570 --> 00:20:40,090
See that? That's the power
of the Go-Home Club.

248
00:20:47,840 --> 00:20:49,160
Oh, go for it, Hiraoka!

249
00:20:49,220 --> 00:20:52,290
- Show us your tournament spirit!
- I won't lose!

250
00:20:53,940 --> 00:20:56,559
Whoever misses has to buy ice cream!

251
00:20:56,560 --> 00:20:58,599
Ah, are you talking about Guchi?

252
00:20:58,600 --> 00:21:00,659
Leave me alone!

253
00:21:00,660 --> 00:21:02,510
Watch me hit a home run!

254
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:04,480
- You jerk!
- Huh?

255
00:21:04,553 --> 00:21:06,843
Buying three ice creams is way too much.

256
00:21:06,890 --> 00:21:08,470
I'm completely broke.

257
00:21:08,510 --> 00:21:10,159
Lately, I've been living on broccoli.

258
00:21:10,160 --> 00:21:11,160
Like I care.

259
00:21:11,161 --> 00:21:13,329
I'm the one who's short on cash.

260
00:21:13,330 --> 00:21:14,559
Being broke is a serious issue.

261
00:21:14,560 --> 00:21:16,360
See you tomorrow, then.

262
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:18,690
- See ya.
- Bye! See you tomorrow.

263
00:21:22,500 --> 00:21:23,860
I'm done. My hands are all red.

264
00:21:25,180 --> 00:21:26,180
Me too.

265
00:21:26,410 --> 00:21:27,450
Wow, that looks painful.

266
00:21:27,490 --> 00:21:29,450
No way. I'm skipping
club activities for a while.

267
00:22:14,290 --> 00:22:15,499
Should we watch this one next time too?

268
00:22:15,500 --> 00:22:17,790
Really? Awesome!

269
00:22:18,090 --> 00:22:20,460
The female lead is indeed really cute.

270
00:22:20,540 --> 00:22:23,380
I don't want to watch it again
just to see her.

271
00:22:23,440 --> 00:22:24,480
No?

272
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:25,800
No...

273
00:22:26,280 --> 00:22:27,680
Well, maybe a little.

274
00:22:28,240 --> 00:22:29,880
But you didn't have to say it out loud...

275
00:22:48,320 --> 00:22:49,660
I'm home.

276
00:22:53,740 --> 00:22:54,910
It's so hot.

277
00:22:58,160 --> 00:22:59,520
Oh, you're back.

278
00:22:59,540 --> 00:23:00,739
You're quite late today.

279
00:23:00,740 --> 00:23:02,299
I went to the batting cages
with Guchi and the guys.

280
00:23:02,300 --> 00:23:04,360
I see. Oh, by the way,

281
00:23:04,380 --> 00:23:06,470
- You've got a letter.
- A letter?

282
00:23:06,510 --> 00:23:07,220
Yeah.

283
00:23:07,300 --> 00:23:08,360
For me?

284
00:23:10,100 --> 00:23:11,100
Here, this one.

285
00:23:12,120 --> 00:23:14,680
It's rare for anyone to
write letters these days.

286
00:23:19,100 --> 00:23:20,100
Wait a minute.

287
00:23:20,440 --> 00:23:21,440
You're being loud!

288
00:23:26,500 --> 00:23:28,500
(Saeki Chiharu)

289
00:23:40,758 --> 00:23:42,371
(Wataru...)

290
00:24:45,690 --> 00:24:48,830
(Next Episode) I thought even if I left,
he wouldn't care that much.

291
00:24:48,900 --> 00:24:51,200
If you don't like it, you can just say so.

292
00:24:51,940 --> 00:24:53,469
Isn't he in Japan right now?

293
00:24:53,470 --> 00:24:55,216
Tell the homeroom
teacher I'm leaving early.

294
00:24:55,240 --> 00:24:59,290
I absolutely refuse
to let this summer end like this.

